				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7059641#post-4203372</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7059641/scp-4660#post-4203372</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 31 Mar 2019 20:20:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>PrLosash</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5257365</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Elan-Vital Energy completely ruins the skip for me.</p> <p>The problem is not the EVE in itself, but the footnote &quot;The fundamental particle of aetheric energy, which powers all thaumatology&quot;. Energy is not a particle, but a property of a particle. Also, there is not such a thing as a spike in particle (there is a &quot;spike in Elan-Vital Energy&quot; in the description).</p> <p>Maybe it would be better if EVE was &quot;One of the components of atheric energy&quot;, or something. Or maybe it just rubs me the wrong way and I am rambling.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7059641#post-4058019</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7059641/scp-4660#post-4058019</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 14 Nov 2018 01:11:23 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>All attempts to remove SCP-4660-2 from SCP-4660-1 result in Buttercup resetting, as it were. Its likely any more aggressive attempts to destroy the collar would result in a similar result if not the death of Buttercup and another reset.</p> <p>As for destroying 4660-3, well, that might work. But the foundation is likely not going to do that for a plethora of reasons, chief among them being that so long as the house stands they know 4660-1 is anchored to that general space, which makes containment relatively simple.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
